ABAKALIKI – The Ebonyi State chapter of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), on Wednesday, held their three-man delegate Congress across the 171 wards of the State. Publicity Secretary of the party in the State, Mr Chika Nwoba, who briefed journalists on the preparation for the exercise, expressed optimism that the three-man delegate congress would be peaceful across the State. He said: “The ad-hoc team that came from Abuja has gone to various local government areas in the State. -Advertisement- “We don’t have any hitch in the 3-man delegate congress, we don’t have any problem whatsoever. “The issue of three-man delegate Congress will be over today because, on the 7th of May, we are having a House of Assembly primary election.” Nwoba said there was no hijack of the Adhoc team or the congress materials sent from the national Secretariat of the party to conduct a three-man delegate congress as being speculated. “Nobody has to hijack anything because the Adhoc team sent from Abuja Secretariat, they have come here. They have met with the INEC. So, where is the hijack coming from? So, nobody has hijacked anything”, the Party’s Spokesman said.